<h1>Problem 1530 - 1988 IMOSL, Hungary 1</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 8</h2>
<p>For what values of \(n\) does there exist an \(n\times n\) array of entries \(-1\), \(0\), or \(1\) such that the \(2n\) sums obtained by summing the elements of the rows and the columns are all different?</p>
